<a class="anchor" id="variables.create"></a>
<div class="documentation">
  <h3>POST /variables</h3>
  <p >Creates a new Variable. </p>
<pre><code class="http">POST https://api.marketcloud.it/v0/variables</code></pre>
<h5>Parameters</h5>
<div class="table-responsive">
  <table class="table table-striped documentation">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>name <span class="label label-success">Required</span></td>
        <td>String</td>
        <td>The variable name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>type</td>
        <td>String</td>
        <td>The data type used to represent this variable, the value can be any of <code>string</code>,<code>number</code>,<code>boolean</code>,<code>object</code>,<code>array</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>value <span class="label label-success">Required</span></td>
        <td>String</td>
        <td>The value of the variable</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table></div>
  <h5>Example Request</h5>
  <pre><code class="bash">curl --request POST
  --url http://api.marketcloud.it/v0/variables \
  --header 'content-type: application/json' \
  --header 'authorization: YourPublicKey:YourToken' \
  --data '{ "name" : "google_analytics_code",   "value" : "UA-12345678",   "type" : "string" }'
  </code></pre>
  <h5>Example JSON response (200)</h5>
  <pre><code class="javascript">{
  "status": true,
  "data": {
    "name": "google_analytics_code",
    "value": "UA-12345678",
    "application_id": 1234,
    "id": 123,
    "updated_at": "2017-08-30T07:07:32.420Z",
    "created_at": "2017-08-30T07:07:32.420Z"
  }
}</code></pre>
</div>
